Fresh Pi session: OPTIONAL REFACTORING / IMPLEMENTATION DESIGN.

Inputs:
- Selected scenario: latest {{run.dir}}/tdd/current-scenario-*.json
- Latest green verification under {{run.dir}}/tdd/
- Prior issues: {{run.issues-file}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Decide whether a small implementation-design improvement is justified now; perform it only when valuable.

Rules:
- Behavior is already green. Do not add behavior or tests for pending scenarios.
- Duplication is a hint, not a command. Avoid speculative abstractions and cleanup beyond this increment.
- If no refactoring is justified, do not edit files and return `no_actions`.
- If refactoring, keep it focused, run relevant tests, and commit it separately when green.
- Do not push or create a PR.

Write:
- Summary and rationale: {{run.dir}}/tdd/refactor-summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/tdd/refactor-status-{{run.round}}.json
- On failure: {{run.dir}}/tdd/refactor-issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"no_actions","summary":"no refactoring justified","issues_file":null}
{"status":"pass","summary":"focused refactoring completed","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"refactoring needs repair","issues_file":"tdd/refactor-issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
